headline: JPMorgan Raises Smurfit Westrock (SW) PT to $61 Amid Q3 2025 Earnings Outlook
summary: Smurfit Westrock (NYSE:SW) is one of the cheap stocks to buy for the next 5 years. On October 6, JPMorgan analyst Detlef Winckelmann raised the firm’s price target on Smurfit Westrock to $61 from $60, while keeping an Overweight rating on the shares. headline: How Analyst Upgrades After the Smurfit Westrock (SW) Merger Have Changed Its Investment Story
summary: In recent days, multiple major analysts issued upgrades and positive outlooks for Smurfit Westrock following its merger, highlighting anticipated stabilization in the containerboard market and improved industry conditions from reduced capacity. This wave of analyst upgrades signals increased market confidence in Smurfit Westrock’s position as the world’s largest containerboard producer and its potential to benefit from shifting supply-demand dynamics globally.
